<HEADLINE>
FT  16 SEP 94 / International Company News: Mayr-Melnhof Karton may offset
materials costs with price rise
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ZURICH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mayr-Melnhof Karton, the Austrian carton board producer, said a sharp
increase in raw materials costs in May would only be offset by price
increases in June and take full effect in the fourth quarter, Reuters
reports from Zurich.
As a result, full-year results are expected to show only a modest
improvement over the first half. Group net profits are seen at Sch140m and
cash flow at Sch920m.
First-half net profits were Sch105m, while full-year profits for 1993 were
Sch117m. Cash flow in the first six months was Sch511m, and Sch831m for the
full year.
'The unprecedented increase in international used paper prices that began in
May has had immediate and unpleasant consequences for the business year
1994,' the company said.
</TEXT>
