<HEADLINE>
FT  16 SEP 94 / Rivers body warns over grant cuts
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Further cuts in government grants for the National Rivers Authority would
cause it 'severe difficulties', Lord Crickhowell, the chairman, said
yesterday.
His comments came as he presented the NRA's annual review, which said that
it was covering more of its costs by charging for services. But some
activities had to be funded by government, for example fishery conservation
and prevention of poaching.
Mr Ed Gallagher, chief executive, said the government grant had fallen from
Pounds 70m last year to Pounds 68m this year. There were indications that it
would be cut to Pounds 60m next year. He said: 'This is about as far as we
can go. If it went any lower it would affect our ability to do our work.'
</TEXT>
