<HEADLINE>
FT  15 SEP 94 / London Stock Exchange: Carlton optimism
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER JOHN, JEFFREY BROWN, STEVE THOMPSON and RAMRAJ GOGNA
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Media group Carlton Communications stood out as the principal bright spot in
the London market as the shares responded to reports of growing advertising
revenue, as well as company presentations to analysts.
Latest industry research shows that forward booking for advertising slots in
October has increased by 6 per cent. The pressure is thought to have come
from the emergence of some big advertisers such as Eurotunnel - ahead of the
opening to the public of the Channel tunnel - and the National Lottery.
There is also the traditional pre-Christmas pick-up.
Analysts pointed out that as there is no need for production costs to rise
the increased demand would translate directly into bottom line profits.
Carlton is the UK's leading independent television group and the stock
received additional support from company presentations ahead of the group's
September year-end. The shares jumped 19 to 875p with turnover higher than
average at 2.2m.
</TEXT>
