<HEADLINE>
FT  15 SEP 94 / UK Company News: Country Casuals chief quits over contract
terms
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PEGGY HOLLINGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Country Casuals, the clothing retailer, yesterday announced the departure of
its chairman and chief executive, Mr John Shannon, just a day after the
group saw more than a fifth of its market value wiped out following a
profits warning.
The group said Mr Shannon resigned when the board refused to extend his
contract. It is believed that Mr Shannon, who was on a one-year rolling
contract, had pressed for a two-year deal. He will be replaced as chief
executive by Mr Mark Bunce, finance director. Mr Tom Adam becomes
non-executive chairman.
Mr Shannon was one of three directors who bought Country Casuals from Coats
Viyella as part of a management buy-out in 1989. He was on a salary of
Pounds 106,000, with a one-year rolling contract, and is expected to receive
a payment of at least Pounds 145,000.
